m)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://outside.clanpages.com/sidepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Prelude to The Companions.</span><hr size=1> Well if you start watching the Roleplay section very soon, you will see an attempt by yours truely to revive the fire in my EQ game.<br>
<br>
Like so many other EQ players at the high end game, I've lost sight of the magic that brought me to this game.  It all becomes numbers, stats, odds, percentages.  And then you stop one night, and realize you've spent 6 or 7 or 8 or 15 hours straight playing EQ, and wonder exactly what you got from it, and how much fun you had getting 2 yellow bubbles (11.5 blue bubbles, xxx number of kills at y camp in z dungeon) in that marathon grind.<br>
<br>
I was talking to a friend last night, about the lastest phat lewt I had gotten.  He doesnt play EQ, so I was reducing it to generic fantasy terms, and I realized how cool some of the stuff actually sounded.<br>
<br>
Peerless Dragonhorn Boots.  Boots made from the horns of a dragon.  Not 18ac, 10agi, 6 vs magic boots.<br>
<br>
Worked Dragonleg Breeches.  Leggings made from the hide of a dragon and the scales from its legs, worked and folded into suitable armor.  Not 21ac, 8dex, 4sta leg armor.<br>
<br>
Ragebringer.  A dagger used by a proffesional assassin, with the innate effect to cause its wielder to go into a trance like battle fury.  Not the rogue epic, with 40% haste effect.<br>
<br>
Armor made of shadows, woven tangible, into wearable armor, stronger than the best man made steel.  Not rogue planar gear.<br>
<br>
Bracers with throwing daggers tucked into hidden slits, not effect:  Summon Throwing Dagger.<br>
<br>
<br>
The game turns into work, get this, go there, do that, Ding!  90 days played in 14 months computes to approximately 40 hours a week playing EQ, on one character.<br>
<br>
It becomes work.<br>
<br>
Price check on Truncheon of Doom.<br>
<br>
So!<br>
<br>
I am beginning a series of fictional stories, based around Ullric Littleblade and those he interacts with.  I wont be asking permission to use a large amount of the characters that will be portraid, since that will simply slow down my creative efforts.  I encourage people who have characters introduced into the continuing plot to add to the stories, and maybe I can flesh out my own little EQ world again.<br>
<br>
Thus is the heralding of The Companions. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=60331"><IMG SRC="http://outside.clanpages.com/ullsig.jpg" border=0></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umairi1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mairi1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/16/01 8:12:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Prelude to The Companions.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It all becomes numbers, stats, odds, percentages.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
