<br>
The rest here is some speculation on what will end up happening:<br>
<br>
1. It will be geared toward the very high lvl players.<br>
   - If this is the case then the high lvl players would show up and try to take out the mob but be surrounded by all the low lvl players and be to lagged to do anything or the zone will crash.<br>
<br>
2. Geared for the mid range lvls 40 to 54<br>
   - Then the high lvl players will show up and one of 2 things will happen A) The mobs will be killed to quickly and those it was geared for will be upset or everyone including those not high enough lvl will show up and crash the zone.<br>
<br>
3. They will try to gear for all lvl's and the zones will be lagged out and crashed. <br>
<br>
In all cases the zones just cannot handle 500 people showing up to the zone. Also since most the high level people do not wish to waste there time getting disconnected, they will not show up and if it is geared towards the high lvl players then Everyone will get lagged and killed.<br>
<br>
Therefore I find  your analysis completely without any real point of true reference. Who the hell wants to have to reconnect every 15 minutes or sit there and have to wait 1 minute to see if your spell landed. While the GM event seem alluring the reality of what will happen makes it unatractive. Plus upon logging in you will find you are dead most likely and have to do a corpse retreival.<br>
<br>
So basically the with those that have taken part in the kithicor war, the thought process is ... Been there, Done that, got the T-shirt.<br>
<br>
